The paper deals with visual grounding, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves the use of novel modules that transform the image-to-query relationship, which can be considered as a machine learning technique (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
